WEBVTT

00:08.965 --> 00:11.924
[soft music]

00:11.968 --> 00:19.671
♪

00:19.715 --> 00:23.153
[background chatter,
laughter]

00:28.724 --> 00:31.466
[police radio chatter]

00:36.471 --> 00:37.907
- And that's his vehicle
right there?

00:37.950 --> 00:40.431
- Yeah, that's his truck.

00:40.475 --> 00:43.782
♪

00:43.826 --> 00:47.395
- Mr. Waters, Enfield police.
Time for you to go.

00:48.396 --> 00:50.615
Come on, Waters,
we know you're home.

00:50.659 --> 00:53.314
- He's probably drunk.

00:53.357 --> 00:55.446
- Okay, chief,
we're coming in.

00:56.882 --> 00:58.101
Son of a bitch.

00:59.102 --> 01:00.451
♪

01:00.495 --> 01:02.192
- [panting]

01:02.236 --> 01:05.891
- Oh, God.
[wheezes, sobs]

01:05.935 --> 01:07.589
Ah, Jesus, no...

01:07.632 --> 01:10.113
Aah!
Oh, Jes--Oh!

01:10.157 --> 01:12.376
- I've been sober two years!

01:12.420 --> 01:13.986
[pants, grunts]

01:14.030 --> 01:16.032
- Oh, God.
Oh!

01:16.076 --> 01:17.686
[sobbing]

01:17.729 --> 01:24.345
♪

01:25.737 --> 01:28.131
- Okay.
Diversity Day is tomorrow,

01:28.175 --> 01:30.829
and I need to bring something
about my culture.

01:30.873 --> 01:32.657
- Something about
your culture...

01:32.701 --> 01:34.268
- I have to share about
our people.

01:34.311 --> 01:36.226
Uh, Grandpa, what do you think
I should bring?

01:36.270 --> 01:40.143
- Hmm, well, you wanna use
my headdress or my tomahawk?

01:40.187 --> 01:41.536
- You have a tomahawk?

01:41.579 --> 01:42.972
- Oh, yeah.

01:43.015 --> 01:46.236
- Don't make jokes.
She's being serious.

01:46.280 --> 01:48.369
Hmm, can it be food?

01:48.412 --> 01:50.414
- No, not food.
- Well, let's look around.

01:50.458 --> 01:52.590
I'm sure we can find something.

01:52.634 --> 01:54.201
[phone buzzes]

01:55.637 --> 01:58.422
[sighs]

01:58.466 --> 02:01.033
- It's okay.

02:01.077 --> 02:04.559
♪

02:04.602 --> 02:07.518
- Today's special
is Reginald Waters, 38.

02:07.562 --> 02:10.042
Killed a police officer
in Enfield, Connecticut

02:10.086 --> 02:13.524
with a shotgun over an eviction
from a rental cabin.

02:13.568 --> 02:15.657
Wounded the landlord
and was last seen driving away

02:15.700 --> 02:17.876
in a blue and white
Ford Lariat pickup.

02:17.920 --> 02:19.661
- We know he left
the state because...

02:19.704 --> 02:22.838
- We don't, but he owns
a home outside Berwick, Maine.

02:22.881 --> 02:26.015
He has one arrest there
for trespassing during protests

02:26.058 --> 02:27.843
against developers
who were building condos

02:27.886 --> 02:29.192
on tribal lands.

02:29.236 --> 02:31.281
He has a rep
for non-violent activism

02:31.325 --> 02:33.327
for Native American causes.

02:33.370 --> 02:35.633
- Our task is to lead
our vigorous,

02:35.677 --> 02:37.766
and by no means,
dying race of people

02:37.809 --> 02:40.377
back to our rightful heritage
of nobility and greatness.

02:40.421 --> 02:42.074
all: Yes!

02:42.118 --> 02:43.815
- We demand to be seen
and to be heard.

02:43.859 --> 02:45.643
all: Yes!

02:45.687 --> 02:47.384
- And to be consulted
in the development of land

02:47.428 --> 02:48.472
that is our birthright.

02:48.516 --> 02:50.170
all: Yes!

02:50.213 --> 02:51.780
- I get his MO.

02:51.823 --> 02:54.304
Speak softly
and carry a big shotgun.

02:54.348 --> 02:56.088
- Besides the trespassing,

02:56.132 --> 02:58.482
he has one domestic disturbance
beef from ten years ago,

02:58.526 --> 03:00.049
around the time of his divorce.

03:00.092 --> 03:02.399
- What is he?
Abenaki Nation?

03:02.443 --> 03:04.096
- No, Mohawk.

03:04.140 --> 03:06.751
He was born on the
Akwesasne reservation upstate.

03:06.795 --> 03:08.579
- The brother's
a wanderer.

03:08.623 --> 03:10.407
- If he wanders to Akwesasne,

03:10.451 --> 03:14.063
all he has to do is walk across
the border to Canada.

03:14.106 --> 03:15.804
- I'll put the word out
to the Indian Country Agents

03:15.847 --> 03:17.501
and the tribal police.

03:17.545 --> 03:19.547
- We know what Waters
was doing in Enfield?

03:19.590 --> 03:20.939
- We don't,
but whatever it was,

03:20.983 --> 03:22.463
it must've been temporary.

03:22.506 --> 03:24.247
He's been renting the cabin
week-to-week,

03:24.291 --> 03:26.423
and his house in Maine has
been empty for five months.

03:26.467 --> 03:27.990
His neighbors have been
watering the plants.

03:28.033 --> 03:29.470
We've got surveillance on it.

03:29.513 --> 03:30.906
- The Enfield police think

03:30.949 --> 03:32.429
Waters killed
one of their officers

03:32.473 --> 03:34.736
over an eviction's notice
for a weekly rental,

03:34.779 --> 03:37.042
and he owns a house in Maine?

03:37.086 --> 03:39.262
Doesn't quite make sense.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.699
- Maybe he has
a low boiling point.

03:41.743 --> 03:43.397
- Something destabilized him,

03:43.440 --> 03:45.268
something he thought
a temporary stint

03:45.312 --> 03:47.662
in Connecticut might resolve.

03:47.705 --> 03:49.141
He was there on a mission.

03:49.185 --> 03:51.579
We need to find out what
that mission was.

03:52.319 --> 03:56.061
- Five months in this shoebox?
- If the price is right.

03:56.105 --> 03:58.150
- Thumbtack holes, fresh.

03:58.194 --> 04:00.501
Looks like Waters set up
some kind of display.

04:00.544 --> 04:02.851
- Leftovers.
Soda.

04:02.894 --> 04:04.940
Living large.

04:04.983 --> 04:07.508
- This was just outside here.

04:07.551 --> 04:10.380
He was trying to burn
something, photos and papers.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.297
- Let's take a look.

04:16.038 --> 04:18.693
[suspenseful music]

04:18.736 --> 04:20.651
♪

04:20.695 --> 04:23.175
- Yeah, I think these are the
photos that were on display.

04:23.219 --> 04:25.134
Looks like a party.

04:25.177 --> 04:28.833
Middle-aged sports fans and
women way out of their league.

04:28.877 --> 04:31.140
- I got a parking lot.

04:31.183 --> 04:32.837
- I got a Raintree Motel.

04:32.881 --> 04:35.536
- I've got receipts.
Lobster for one.

04:35.579 --> 04:38.843
And this looks like it's from a
hotel in Houston last October.

04:38.887 --> 04:41.019
- Right,
during the World Series.

04:41.063 --> 04:43.370
- This photo was taken
from inside a car.

04:43.413 --> 04:45.415
The driver was behind
the wheel

04:45.459 --> 04:47.678
and got a piece
of the side view mirror

04:47.722 --> 04:49.550
in the photo.

04:49.593 --> 04:52.335
He also caught a reflection
of himself holding the camera.

04:52.379 --> 04:55.033
- That's not Waters.

04:55.077 --> 05:00.474
- The circles around the faces,
clandestine locations.

05:00.517 --> 05:04.913
These are surveillance photos
taken by this guy, maybe a PI.

05:04.956 --> 05:07.524
- There is a Raintree Motel
15 minutes from here

05:07.568 --> 05:10.092
just across the state line
in Springfield, Massachusetts.

05:10.135 --> 05:11.963
This PI's probably local.

05:12.007 --> 05:15.663
- A hotshot who gets his own
face in a surveillance photo?

05:15.706 --> 05:17.012
Should be easy to find.

05:17.055 --> 05:18.405
- Let's do it.

05:18.448 --> 05:20.058
- Yup, that's me.

05:20.102 --> 05:22.931
Should've used a telephoto lens
on that photo.

05:22.974 --> 05:24.585
[chuckles]

05:24.628 --> 05:26.456
Reg, he goes by Reg.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.545
He hired me to find
his daughter.

05:28.589 --> 05:30.460
She disappeared
about six months ago.

05:30.504 --> 05:32.593
- And she disappeared here
in Springfield?

05:32.636 --> 05:34.421
- Reg was raising her up
in Maine, alone,

05:34.464 --> 05:36.161
after his wife died.

05:36.205 --> 05:38.207
The daughter and him,
they weren't getting along,

05:38.250 --> 05:40.514
so, minute she turned 18,

05:40.557 --> 05:44.169
she took off down here
with her boyfriend.

05:44.213 --> 05:45.823
They moved into the
Raintree Motel.

05:45.867 --> 05:48.260
It's a dump.
A month later, she was gone.

05:48.304 --> 05:50.393
- And you went to Houston
to find...

05:50.437 --> 05:52.047
and I assume the daughter
has a name.

05:52.090 --> 05:54.266
- Audrey.
Yeah.

05:54.310 --> 05:56.617
Reg thought she might've
been sex-trafficked.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.445
That's why I went to Houston.

05:58.488 --> 06:01.665
Big sports events, they're like
magnets for sex traffickers.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.232
- Sounds like that needle
in a haystack.

06:03.275 --> 06:04.973
- Oh, no, no.
I have this software.

06:05.016 --> 06:06.627
You plug in a description
of a girl,

06:06.670 --> 06:09.281
like a redhead with
a tramp stamp,

06:09.325 --> 06:12.981
and the algorithm scans
thousands of escort ads.

06:14.461 --> 06:18.465
- The algorithm told you to go
to Houston, all expenses paid,

06:18.508 --> 06:20.989
and 10,000 bucks later,
you had nothing to show Reg.

06:21.032 --> 06:22.686
You cleaned him out, Mr. Vans.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.340
It's a wonder
he didn't shoot you.

06:24.384 --> 06:25.559
- [chuckling]
That's not fair.

06:25.602 --> 06:27.430
I shared that software
with him.

06:27.474 --> 06:29.519
I mean, that's got to be worth
at least a couple of grand.

06:29.563 --> 06:31.216
- I'm sure.

06:31.260 --> 06:33.001
Any idea where he might go?

06:33.044 --> 06:35.133
- No, I haven't talked to him
in a week.

06:35.177 --> 06:36.439
- What about Audrey's
boyfriend?

06:36.483 --> 06:38.398
Is he a suspect
in her disappearance?

06:38.441 --> 06:40.008
- Jeremy?
No.

06:40.051 --> 06:42.750
He, uh, he called Reg
after she went missing.

06:42.793 --> 06:44.621
He's a musician.

06:44.665 --> 06:47.668
His story is that he went back
to the motel after a gig

06:47.711 --> 06:49.409
and she was gone.

06:49.452 --> 06:51.062
- And where can we find Jeremy?

06:51.106 --> 06:52.586
- Somewhere in Maine.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.414
- Somewhere in Maine.
That's the best you can do?

06:54.457 --> 06:56.154
- Yeah, I wasn't paid
to find the boyfriend.

06:56.198 --> 06:59.854
- I'm sure you can find him if
the NBA Finals were in Maine.

07:00.811 --> 07:02.465
- Audrey Waters' disappearance

07:02.509 --> 07:04.511
is still
an active investigation.

07:04.554 --> 07:06.469
We haven't given up,
and we don't plan to,

07:06.513 --> 07:08.123
no matter what
her father's done.

07:08.166 --> 07:09.516
- That's good to hear.

07:09.559 --> 07:10.952
Do you have any idea why Waters

07:10.995 --> 07:12.649
shot down an officer
in Enfield?

07:12.693 --> 07:14.129
- It was over an eviction,
wasn't it?

07:14.172 --> 07:16.392
- We don't think so.
It's against character.

07:17.480 --> 07:19.439
- I heard he might've been
drinking.

07:19.482 --> 07:21.441
- There's no evidence
of that.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.878
- You met him--did he seem
like a drunk to you?

07:23.921 --> 07:25.488
- I couldn't tell.

07:25.532 --> 07:26.750
He was very distressed
about his daughter.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.752
- Captain, it would help us

07:28.796 --> 07:30.754
if we could take a look
at her file.

07:30.798 --> 07:33.496
- Of course, but the lead
detective retired last month.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.280
I'll call him.

07:35.324 --> 07:36.717
- I thought it was
an active case.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.283
- People retire.
What can I say?

07:38.327 --> 07:39.720
- Of course.

07:39.763 --> 07:41.722
You mind asking
that young police aide

07:41.765 --> 07:43.680
to bring me a cup of coffee?

07:43.724 --> 07:44.725
- Yeah.

07:48.729 --> 07:50.470
Dottie, can you bring in
a coffee?

07:50.513 --> 07:51.862
- Uh, black, two sugars.

07:51.906 --> 07:54.648
- Black,
two sugars.

07:54.691 --> 07:56.171
So when I hear back
from the detective,

07:56.214 --> 07:58.303
I'll reach out to you.

07:58.347 --> 08:01.089
I heard he's fishing out
in Quebec for walleye.

08:01.959 --> 08:05.441
- I know a few spots up there.
You fish?

08:06.311 --> 08:08.662
- [clears throat]
I hunt.

08:08.705 --> 08:10.228
Waterfowl, ducks.

08:10.272 --> 08:11.926
- We found some calls

08:11.969 --> 08:14.494
Waters made to this precinct
after hours.

08:14.537 --> 08:17.584
10, 15- minute calls.
All this month.

08:17.627 --> 08:18.802
Thank you.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.195
- Dottie.

08:20.238 --> 08:21.718
Well,
he didn't talk to me.

08:21.762 --> 08:24.068
Probably got an update
from the lead detective.

08:24.112 --> 08:26.549
- The one who retired
last month?

08:26.593 --> 08:28.856
This is delicious,
by the way.

08:28.899 --> 08:31.380
Thank you, Miss...
- Boruta.

08:31.423 --> 08:38.169
♪

08:41.390 --> 08:43.566
- Miss Boruta.

08:43.610 --> 08:46.395
♪

08:46.438 --> 08:49.311
We don't want to get you
in trouble with your boss,

08:49.354 --> 08:52.183
but those phone calls--Waters
was talking to you, wasn't he?

08:52.227 --> 08:55.535
- I felt sorry for him,
but that's it.

08:55.578 --> 08:59.060
- You talked to him because the
others wouldn't listen, right?

08:59.103 --> 09:00.714
- They didn't try.

09:00.757 --> 09:03.151
Not the police,
not that private detective.

09:03.194 --> 09:06.154
- Why, did they think
Audrey ran away on her own?

09:06.197 --> 09:08.765
- They didn't care
because she's Native American.

09:08.809 --> 09:11.159
They just called her
a prostitute and a junkie,

09:11.202 --> 09:14.162
and that was that,
but she wasn't.

09:14.205 --> 09:16.991
They're just bigots.

09:18.775 --> 09:20.777
- You tried to help Reg?

09:20.821 --> 09:23.432
- I gave him a copy
of Audrey's file.

09:23.475 --> 09:25.216
The file was so thin.

09:25.260 --> 09:29.438
It just devastated Reg to see
how little the police had done.

09:29.481 --> 09:34.008
And then the very next day,
he shot those people.

09:35.487 --> 09:36.750
It's my fault.

09:36.793 --> 09:38.969
I didn't know
how angry he'd be.

09:39.013 --> 09:41.232
- Did you keep a copy
of the file?

09:41.276 --> 09:48.283
♪

09:55.682 --> 09:57.205
- You know, you can buy
your own cigarettes

09:57.248 --> 09:58.641
every now and then.
- I need to see the guest

09:58.685 --> 10:00.948
register from last June.
- Excuse me?

10:03.124 --> 10:04.778
The only thing
I'm offering is rooms, man.

10:06.170 --> 10:08.085
You want one?

10:08.129 --> 10:09.957
- Look, my daughter
stayed here in June.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.349
She was kidnapped.

10:11.393 --> 10:13.351
- Sounds serious.
You should call 911.

10:13.395 --> 10:15.658
- [chuckles]

10:15.702 --> 10:18.356
- Show me the register now.

10:18.400 --> 10:20.315
- All right, dude,
you're screwed.

10:23.100 --> 10:25.320
- No, no, dude,
don't shoot me, no--

10:32.370 --> 10:35.635
[police radio chatter]

10:35.678 --> 10:38.638
- He checked the guest register
for last June.

10:38.681 --> 10:40.074
- When his daughter was here.

10:40.117 --> 10:41.553
- He's got the police file,

10:41.597 --> 10:43.468
and he knows the leads
they didn't follow.

10:43.512 --> 10:44.992
- Well, looks like
he's following them now.

10:45.035 --> 10:47.255
- With a vengeance.
Everyone's failed him.

10:47.298 --> 10:50.432
He must feel very alone
right now,

10:50.475 --> 10:52.956
as if he's the only one that
could find his daughter.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.480
Anybody gets in the way...

10:55.524 --> 10:58.440
and they won't live
to tell about it.

10:58.483 --> 11:00.616
We have the road map now.

11:01.791 --> 11:04.011
Let's get ahead of him.

11:04.054 --> 11:10.017
♪

11:15.283 --> 11:17.111
- Adams?
- Yeah.

11:17.154 --> 11:18.852
- Ten pages.

11:18.895 --> 11:22.333
That's the whole file
for a six-month investigation.

11:22.377 --> 11:24.466
- Police didn't even put
Audrey Waters' DNA

11:24.509 --> 11:26.816
into NAMUS for a match
to unclaimed remains.

11:28.339 --> 11:30.080
- I'll get on it.

11:30.124 --> 11:32.213
- Looks like Cops in Enfield
dropped the ball on a tip.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.432
A girl matching
Audrey's description

11:34.476 --> 11:36.739
was seen selling jewelry
in a farmer's market in town.

11:36.783 --> 11:39.263
This must've put Reg
in a very good mood

11:39.307 --> 11:41.178
when the Enfield cop
showed up to evict him.

11:41.222 --> 11:43.703
- Reg probably thinks these
cops are equally responsible

11:43.746 --> 11:46.096
for his girl's disappearance.

11:46.140 --> 11:47.794
No wonder he went to war
against them.

11:47.837 --> 11:49.839
- Here's another lead
they dropped.

11:49.883 --> 11:53.277
Page five--Audrey's boyfriend
Jeremy told the police

11:53.321 --> 11:55.105
about a white pimp named Lex

11:55.149 --> 11:57.368
who was a couple of doors down
from him at the Raintree.

11:57.412 --> 11:59.980
He had two girls with him,
one white, one Asian.

12:00.023 --> 12:02.199
Jeremy said Lex and the girls
had checked out

12:02.243 --> 12:04.941
by the time he got home
and found Audrey missing.

12:04.985 --> 12:07.857
No record Springfield PD
ever followed up.

12:07.901 --> 12:09.119
- I'll follow up.

12:09.163 --> 12:11.469
A pimp named Lex
works the northeast.

12:11.513 --> 12:13.907
- That explains why Reg
checked the motel register.

12:13.950 --> 12:16.474
- No forwarding address
for the boyfriend.

12:16.518 --> 12:18.172
Springfield didn't even
keep tabs on him.

12:18.215 --> 12:20.174
- Most likely Reg will be
on his way up to Maine

12:20.217 --> 12:21.697
to look for him.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.525
- Find Jeremy.

12:23.568 --> 12:27.355
In the meantime, if I were Reg,
I'd try to hit home base first.

12:28.835 --> 12:30.967
♪

12:31.011 --> 12:33.317
- I got stuff from Audrey's old
room they can pull DNA from.

12:33.361 --> 12:35.450
- Good.

12:35.493 --> 12:37.757
The dust impressions
under this frame...

12:39.802 --> 12:41.804
It's been moved recently.

12:51.901 --> 12:53.642
- This is Paula
and Cody Sampson.

12:53.685 --> 12:56.166
They're taking care
of Reg's place.

12:56.210 --> 12:58.473
- I'm Jess LaCroix.

12:58.516 --> 13:00.867
Have you seen or spoken
to Reg lately?

13:00.910 --> 13:02.782
- We just take care
of the house.

13:02.825 --> 13:04.522
- Make sure the pipes
don't freeze.

13:04.566 --> 13:06.698
- It's hard to believe he did
what they're accusing him of.

13:06.742 --> 13:08.483
- We don't have anything to do
with that.

13:08.526 --> 13:11.486
We're just trying to find him
before more people get hurt.

13:15.185 --> 13:17.448
- There's a safe under there.

13:17.492 --> 13:19.842
Somebody's been in it recently.

13:19.886 --> 13:21.626
If I run the prints on it,

13:21.670 --> 13:24.194
they'll come back to one
of you, won't they?

13:26.936 --> 13:28.633
- If you're
straight up with us,

13:28.677 --> 13:31.288
we won't have any problems.

13:31.332 --> 13:34.596
- I took money out yesterday--
all of it, $3,000--

13:34.639 --> 13:36.337
and gave it to Reg.

13:36.380 --> 13:38.861
I know what he did,
but I love him like a brother.

13:38.905 --> 13:41.037
Nothing can change that.

13:41.081 --> 13:42.909
- Fair enough.

13:42.952 --> 13:44.519
Did he tell you
where he was going?

13:44.562 --> 13:46.129
- No.

13:46.173 --> 13:48.784
I, uh, I don't think
he knows himself.

13:48.828 --> 13:52.266
He's been on a broken road
a long time.

13:52.309 --> 13:54.398
- Tell me.

13:54.442 --> 13:57.749
♪

13:57.793 --> 13:59.882
- Reg wasn't a good father
to Audrey.

13:59.926 --> 14:02.450
He walked out on her mother
when she was seven.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.626
He was drinking then.
- And he stopped?

14:04.669 --> 14:09.631
- Two years ago after Audrey's
mother, Diane, killed herself.

14:09.674 --> 14:12.112
Audrey came to live with him.
It was a disaster.

14:12.155 --> 14:15.506
- Reg tried everything
to make it right with Audrey,

14:15.550 --> 14:18.031
but he couldn't be
a good parent to her.

14:18.074 --> 14:20.511
A man like Reg...
he didn't know how.

14:20.555 --> 14:22.209
♪

14:22.252 --> 14:24.341
- I'm raising my daughter
on my own,

14:24.385 --> 14:26.735
so I understand.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.215
♪

14:28.258 --> 14:30.347
- I think this is different.

14:30.391 --> 14:32.349
This is about the schools.

14:32.393 --> 14:34.656
- He won't understand.

14:34.699 --> 14:37.093
- He was married to my sister.
Try him.

14:39.400 --> 14:42.359
- Reg's father and my father
were in Indian school together.

14:42.403 --> 14:44.013
Residential schools.

14:44.057 --> 14:45.710
They were taken
from their parents

14:45.754 --> 14:47.451
when they were little
and sent there.

14:47.495 --> 14:50.193
You know what the priests
and nuns did to them in there?

14:50.237 --> 14:51.891
- I know the motto.

14:51.934 --> 14:54.197
"Kill the Indian
to save the man."

14:54.241 --> 14:58.027
- And worse.
Physical and sexual abuse.

14:58.071 --> 15:01.204
Little kids, man,
in that school for ten years.

15:03.380 --> 15:04.904
How could our fathers grow up

15:04.947 --> 15:06.688
and be good parents to us
after that,

15:06.731 --> 15:08.429
when no one parented them?

15:08.472 --> 15:09.821
- It's a bad cycle,

15:09.865 --> 15:12.520
and Reg is just caught up
in it.

15:14.130 --> 15:16.480
- Thanks for talking to us.

15:16.524 --> 15:19.483
[somber music]

15:19.527 --> 15:26.273
♪

15:26.316 --> 15:28.057
- I found the boyfriend
Jeremy.

15:28.101 --> 15:31.017
He's just been released
from the hospital.

15:31.060 --> 15:32.801
- Good.

15:33.889 --> 15:36.587
- I just moved in,
and Reg shows up.

15:36.631 --> 15:38.894
He was all pissed off
because I never told him

15:38.938 --> 15:40.983
about the people at the motel.

15:41.027 --> 15:42.680
He beat the crap out of me.

15:42.724 --> 15:44.378
He thought
I was holding out on him.

15:44.421 --> 15:46.815
- People at the motel,
you mean that pimp, Lex?

15:46.858 --> 15:49.644
- Yeah, and the two girls.

15:49.687 --> 15:52.603
- You tell Reg anything
about where he could find Lex?

15:52.647 --> 15:54.910
Maybe something
you didn't tell the cops?

15:54.954 --> 15:57.565
- Reg wanted names.
All I knew was Lex.

15:57.608 --> 16:00.220
Oh, and the Asian girl,
she was called Blue.

16:00.263 --> 16:01.351
It's probably not real.

16:01.395 --> 16:02.700
- And you know her name

16:02.744 --> 16:04.746
because you talked to her,
right?

16:04.789 --> 16:07.009
What else did you tell Reg
about her?

16:07.053 --> 16:10.143
- Just about her earlobe,
it was all messed up.

16:10.186 --> 16:11.753
Like torn.

16:11.796 --> 16:15.626
She said it was from Lex
ripping her earring off.

16:18.455 --> 16:21.110
- So we're looking
for an Asian escort,

16:21.154 --> 16:24.026
nom de guerre Blue,
early to mid-20s,

16:24.070 --> 16:26.986
East Coast,
with a deformed earlobe.

16:27.029 --> 16:29.510
♪

16:29.553 --> 16:31.381
- How good can this thing be?

16:31.425 --> 16:33.035
- Well, I don't know.

16:33.079 --> 16:36.299
I haven't used an app
to find an escort before.

16:36.343 --> 16:38.998
So we have some contenders.

16:39.041 --> 16:40.869
This one has a neck tattoo.

16:40.912 --> 16:42.958
- I think Jeremy
would've mentioned that.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.439
♪

16:45.482 --> 16:47.354
- This one, Angela Blue,

16:47.397 --> 16:49.791
her hair is covering
her earlobes.

16:50.661 --> 16:52.272
- Will you blow that up?

16:52.315 --> 16:54.013
[mouse clicks]

16:55.579 --> 16:57.016
Yeah.

16:57.973 --> 17:00.671
Her earlobe
looks photoshopped.

17:00.715 --> 17:02.543
- She's in Hagerstown,
Maryland.

17:03.761 --> 17:05.328
- Let's make a date.

17:05.372 --> 17:06.895
[police radio chatter]

17:06.938 --> 17:08.505
- Deceased is Rodney Brock,
aka Hot Rod,

17:08.549 --> 17:10.072
priors for sex trafficking.

17:10.116 --> 17:11.552
Somebody opened him up
with a knife.

17:11.595 --> 17:13.380
Wits ID'd your guy
Reginald Waters.

17:13.423 --> 17:15.295
- You have Brock's photo?

17:16.252 --> 17:18.385
Lex is white.
Reg killed the wrong pimp.

17:18.428 --> 17:19.951
- The girls with Brock,
any of them Asian?

17:19.995 --> 17:21.605
- Funny you should ask.

17:21.649 --> 17:23.607
Your guy Waters grabbed an
Asian pro that was with Brock,

17:23.651 --> 17:24.956
name of Angela Blue.

17:25.000 --> 17:27.220
- Any distinguishing marks
on this woman?

17:27.263 --> 17:29.091
- Apparently,
she has a messed-up ear.

17:29.135 --> 17:31.093
But that'll be the least
of her worries now.

17:31.137 --> 17:36.707
♪

17:36.751 --> 17:38.361
- He came in the room.

17:38.405 --> 17:40.059
He had a big knife.

17:41.756 --> 17:44.019
He grabbed Angela
and dragged her out.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.803
- Did he say
where he was taking her?

17:45.847 --> 17:48.328
- "Come with me."
That's all he said.

17:49.633 --> 17:52.767
- And what about this girl?
Her name's Audrey.

17:52.810 --> 17:56.292
The man who took Angela,
that's his daughter.

17:56.336 --> 17:58.120
He's looking for her.

17:58.164 --> 18:01.515
- No, don't know her.
She's lucky.

18:01.558 --> 18:02.820
- Why is that?

18:02.864 --> 18:05.127
- Someone's looking for her.

18:05.171 --> 18:09.479
♪

18:09.523 --> 18:12.003
- Well, thank you.
Take care of yourselves.

18:12.047 --> 18:13.962
- Thank you.

18:14.005 --> 18:17.357
- Another murder, a kidnapping.
Reg is getting more desperate.

18:17.400 --> 18:19.881
And I hope for her sake

18:19.924 --> 18:22.231
that Angela has
some answers for him.

18:39.901 --> 18:43.774
- I'm sorry about...you know?

18:45.036 --> 18:46.473
- Wait.

18:48.039 --> 18:49.780
Take this.

18:51.042 --> 18:52.305
Call your parents.

18:52.348 --> 18:54.568
They're probably
looking for you.

18:55.917 --> 18:58.528
- Audrey said you were
a really good dad.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.663
- I wasn't.

19:02.706 --> 19:05.796
[somber music]

19:05.840 --> 19:10.366
♪

19:10.410 --> 19:12.238
[sighs]

19:12.281 --> 19:17.982
♪

19:18.026 --> 19:20.985
[sobs, yells]

19:21.029 --> 19:26.121
♪

19:33.520 --> 19:36.218
- Nothing at the checkpoints.

19:36.262 --> 19:38.177
New pic of my niece?

19:38.220 --> 19:42.093
- Yeah, from Diversity Day
at school.

19:46.185 --> 19:49.057
You know, I heard about
the residential schools,

19:49.100 --> 19:51.712
but I never asked Marilou
and Nelson about them.

19:53.322 --> 19:54.932
- They didn't go.

19:54.976 --> 19:57.196
Their parents
kept them at home,

19:57.239 --> 19:59.067
hid them from the priests
when they came along.

19:59.110 --> 20:00.634
They're lucky.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.853
My dad had a couple
of uncles that went.

20:02.897 --> 20:04.638
Those guys are haunted.

20:04.681 --> 20:06.248
- Did they have kids?

20:06.292 --> 20:09.077
- Yeah, a few,
and they had kids.

20:09.120 --> 20:11.166
They're all a little bit
messed up.

20:11.210 --> 20:14.387
Multigenerational trauma.

20:14.430 --> 20:16.998
- Man hands misery to man.

20:17.041 --> 20:20.175
Nobody heals,
they just keep passing it on.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.046
- [sighs]
You can't make a kid

20:22.090 --> 20:25.398
feel loved and safe if
you've never experienced that.

20:25.441 --> 20:29.097
♪

20:29.140 --> 20:31.534
I know what
you're thinking, bro.

20:31.578 --> 20:35.059
About your old man.
What he passed on to you.

20:35.103 --> 20:37.236
- What I might pass on
to Tali?

20:37.279 --> 20:40.500
- No, I mean,
how she cares for animals.

20:40.543 --> 20:43.459
She cares because
she's been cared for.

20:43.503 --> 20:45.722
You hear what I'm saying,
bro?

20:46.680 --> 20:48.203
Tali's gonna be okay.

20:48.247 --> 20:50.684
♪

20:50.727 --> 20:54.427
- Staties found Angela.
She's safe.

20:54.470 --> 20:56.690
Reg dropped her off
at a gas station.

20:56.733 --> 21:00.302
[suspenseful music]

21:00.346 --> 21:02.870
- No harm, no foul, okay?
Thanks.

21:02.913 --> 21:05.612
It's over.
I want to go.

21:05.655 --> 21:07.309
- I understand
you're a survivor

21:07.353 --> 21:08.832
and that's how you cope.

21:08.876 --> 21:10.921
You dust yourself off
and you move on.

21:10.965 --> 21:12.401
- Basically, yeah.

21:13.707 --> 21:15.099
- And we respect that,

21:15.143 --> 21:16.797
but we need you
to help us find Reg

21:16.840 --> 21:18.668
before he harms anyone else.

21:18.712 --> 21:20.104
- He didn't harm me.

21:20.148 --> 21:22.106
He just wanted some intel,

21:22.150 --> 21:24.326
and once he got it,
he let me go.

21:24.370 --> 21:26.023
- What'd you tell him?

21:26.067 --> 21:27.677
- I told him what I heard.

21:27.721 --> 21:29.200
That Audrey was killed
by a john

21:29.244 --> 21:31.159
and Lex got rid of her body.

21:31.202 --> 21:32.465
I don't know where.

21:32.508 --> 21:34.205
- Were you there
when Lex kidnapped her?

21:34.249 --> 21:35.903
- Yeah.

21:35.946 --> 21:40.255
He chatted her up,
gave her a beer, roofied her.

21:40.299 --> 21:42.344
We tried to get him
to leave her at the motel,

21:42.388 --> 21:46.174
but I didn't want
my other ear ripped off.

21:48.176 --> 21:50.700
- Reg would've been devastated
to hear all this.

21:50.744 --> 21:52.441
He'd want to find Lex

21:52.485 --> 21:55.314
and he'd want to find
Audrey's remains.

21:55.357 --> 21:57.359
Were you able to help him
with any of that?

21:57.403 --> 22:00.057
- Lex had a real serious
drug problem.

22:00.101 --> 22:02.364
He got so strung out
he couldn't function.

22:02.408 --> 22:04.497
He had to go stay with
his family in Pittsburgh.

22:05.672 --> 22:06.890
- You know his real name?

22:06.934 --> 22:08.892
- I know more than that.

22:08.936 --> 22:11.025
I have a picture
of his driver's license.

22:11.068 --> 22:14.942
♪

22:14.985 --> 22:17.510
- Felix Erbe.
How'd you get this?

22:17.553 --> 22:20.077
- Someone was gonna die because
of Lex's drug problem.

22:20.121 --> 22:21.818
It seemed like something
I should have.

22:21.862 --> 22:24.168
- Did you show that to Reg?
- Yeah.

22:24.212 --> 22:27.041
He, uh,
he wrote everything down.

22:27.084 --> 22:29.957
♪

22:30.000 --> 22:31.785
- Let's find him.

22:31.828 --> 22:34.135
♪

22:34.178 --> 22:35.832
- That's what's left
of my brother.

22:35.876 --> 22:39.140
They found him two weeks ago
off Brownsville Road.

22:39.183 --> 22:41.316
Drug overdose.

22:41.360 --> 22:43.405
I don't know what
to do with his ashes.

22:43.449 --> 22:44.798
- Well, I'm very sorry.

22:44.841 --> 22:46.887
- There's nothing
to be sorry for.

22:46.930 --> 22:48.889
Felix got off easy,
all things considered.

22:49.977 --> 22:51.935
- Has anybody been here
asking about him?

22:51.979 --> 22:53.850
- This one man yesterday.

22:53.894 --> 22:56.723
Said his daughter was
sex trafficked by Felix.

22:56.766 --> 22:58.464
- This guy?

22:58.507 --> 23:00.204
- Yeah, that's him.
Reg.

23:01.380 --> 23:03.164
Oh, my God.

23:03.207 --> 23:06.776
I let him in my house.
I sat right here with him.

23:06.820 --> 23:08.474
- Was he threatening
or menacing?

23:08.517 --> 23:10.998
- No, he was just sad.

23:11.041 --> 23:13.522
Look, I know who
my brother was,

23:13.566 --> 23:15.350
what he did to women.

23:15.394 --> 23:17.787
And I'm not into forgiveness,
at least not for Felix.

23:17.831 --> 23:21.008
So when Reg told me what Felix
did to his daughter,

23:21.051 --> 23:23.619
I was just...

23:23.663 --> 23:25.708
said I'm sorry.

23:25.752 --> 23:28.581
I'm so sorry because I am.

23:28.624 --> 23:31.148
- Is that all he wanted?
Just to talk?

23:31.192 --> 23:33.020
- I think Reg was
maybe hoping

23:33.063 --> 23:35.675
to find an answer
about his daughter.

23:35.718 --> 23:38.155
- And there was nothing?

23:38.199 --> 23:39.853
It must've been a blow to him.

23:39.896 --> 23:41.681
- He said it was like
the end of the road.

23:41.724 --> 23:46.163
Then I saw his eyes were wet
and then I started crying.

23:46.207 --> 23:49.166
[somber music]

23:49.210 --> 23:53.693
Honestly, all this talk
about my brother just...

23:53.736 --> 23:57.131
Reg said I shouldn't
blame myself.

23:57.174 --> 23:59.655
- He's right.
What else did he say?

23:59.699 --> 24:01.875
- He said whatever made
my brother a monster

24:01.918 --> 24:03.354
happened a long time ago.

24:03.398 --> 24:05.922
Told me to burn
my brother's things,

24:05.966 --> 24:08.925
that it would
break the cycle of pain

24:08.969 --> 24:11.624
and give me an ending.

24:11.667 --> 24:13.364
I don't know.

24:13.408 --> 24:15.149
It was fine.

24:15.192 --> 24:17.151
He left without any trouble.

24:17.194 --> 24:19.545
- Did he give you any idea
where he might be going?

24:19.588 --> 24:23.853
- No, he said he had to do
his own work to heal the past.

24:23.897 --> 24:25.289
- In those words?

24:25.333 --> 24:26.508
- Yup.

24:28.902 --> 24:30.947
I'm sorry.
All this talk...

24:30.991 --> 24:33.559
I need a minute.
Excuse me.

24:36.126 --> 24:38.215
- Heal the past.

24:38.259 --> 24:39.869
- His wife's suicide,

24:39.913 --> 24:43.873
his failure as a parent
and as a husband,

24:43.917 --> 24:46.397
Audrey's murder.

24:46.441 --> 24:50.445
He's hit a dead end.
He's turning back on himself.

24:50.489 --> 24:52.578
- He wants to break the cycle.

24:52.621 --> 24:54.841
If I were him,
I'd go see my father.

24:54.884 --> 24:58.540
[suspenseful music]

24:58.584 --> 25:05.895
♪

25:05.939 --> 25:07.984
- Rickey!

25:08.028 --> 25:09.769
Come here!

25:10.944 --> 25:13.337
You come when I call you.

25:14.861 --> 25:16.079
Get inside.

25:16.123 --> 25:17.820
Go cry to your mother.
- Ow!

25:17.864 --> 25:24.566
♪

25:35.490 --> 25:37.710
- We've kept an eye
on Leonard's house.

25:37.753 --> 25:40.060
Not 24/7.
Too much to do

25:40.103 --> 25:42.018
and not enough officers
to do it with.

25:42.062 --> 25:44.934
- We have Indian Country
agents available.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.023
- They're good when a crime's
been committed on the Rez,

25:47.067 --> 25:49.112
but no crime's
been committed here.

25:49.156 --> 25:52.507
And the idea of the FBI
setting up camp on our land

25:52.551 --> 25:54.465
outside our people's homes?

25:54.509 --> 25:56.119
Not gonna happen.

25:56.163 --> 25:58.644
- What's the issue between Reg
and his father?

25:58.687 --> 26:00.428
- Rocky.

26:00.471 --> 26:02.604
I don't think Reg'd get
a helping hand from his dad.

26:02.648 --> 26:05.912
He hasn't been around much
since his mother passed.

26:05.955 --> 26:07.870
Leonard's remarried.

26:07.914 --> 26:11.918
Reg has a half-brother now,
Rickey.

26:15.922 --> 26:17.271
- You should know better,
Shane,

26:17.314 --> 26:18.881
to bring the FBI
into my house.

26:18.925 --> 26:20.579
What's the use
of having tribal police

26:20.622 --> 26:22.450
if every time somebody
stubs their toe,

26:22.493 --> 26:24.017
you go running to the Feds?

26:24.060 --> 26:26.497
- Leonard,
just answer their questions.

26:27.411 --> 26:29.239
- Didn't you tell them that
Reg and I don't get along?

26:29.283 --> 26:30.676
- You did, Mr. Waters,

26:30.719 --> 26:32.460
but you know how angry
Reg gets.

26:32.503 --> 26:34.636
We came to warn you
that he might be coming here.

26:34.680 --> 26:36.812
- Oh, so now the government
wants to protect me?

26:36.856 --> 26:38.335
That's a funny one.

26:38.379 --> 26:40.990
- Yeah, it's funny,
but that's our job.

26:41.034 --> 26:43.210
Reg told someone he wanted
to break the cycle.

26:43.253 --> 26:44.777
We thought he might
start with you.

26:44.820 --> 26:46.779
- Let him come.
You know, he blames me

26:46.822 --> 26:48.694
because
he was no kind of husband,

26:48.737 --> 26:50.696
no kind of father to Audrey.

26:50.739 --> 26:52.306
He never just
let anything be.

26:52.349 --> 26:54.047
He's always raising Cain.

26:54.090 --> 26:55.744
- And you look like
a scrapper yourself.

26:55.788 --> 26:58.138
Those scratches on your neck?
How'd you get those?

26:59.661 --> 27:01.445
- My wife's
a very passionate woman.

27:03.796 --> 27:06.842
- Or maybe it was from
your other son, Rickey.

27:06.886 --> 27:08.801
Where is he anyway?

27:08.844 --> 27:10.672
♪

27:10.716 --> 27:13.240
- He's around,
riding his bike.

27:13.283 --> 27:15.982
- His bike is outside.

27:16.025 --> 27:18.941
[speaks in Mohawk]

27:18.985 --> 27:20.682
- Reg took him.

27:20.726 --> 27:22.379
Reg was here this morning,

27:22.423 --> 27:23.859
he had a big fight
with Leonard.

27:23.903 --> 27:25.469
I took Leonard inside
to stop the fight,

27:25.513 --> 27:27.994
and when I went back out,
Reg was gone with Rickey.

27:28.037 --> 27:29.822
He wouldn't let me
call the police.

27:29.865 --> 27:31.693
He wanted to protect Reg

27:31.737 --> 27:34.957
because he thinks that's what
a dad's supposed to do,

27:35.001 --> 27:37.612
but you didn't protect Rickey.

27:37.656 --> 27:44.663
♪

27:45.359 --> 27:47.100
- His name is Rickey Waters,

27:47.143 --> 27:49.842
ten years old, 4'10",
75 pounds.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.757
Last seen wearing
a green hoodie,

27:51.800 --> 27:53.193
light gray parka
and running shoes.

27:53.236 --> 27:54.803
- Got all that.

27:54.847 --> 27:56.587
- All right, passing it on
to Homeland security

27:56.631 --> 27:58.285
and New York State Police.

27:58.328 --> 28:00.200
- I've alerted the detachment
on the Canadian side

28:00.243 --> 28:02.028
of the reservation.
- Appreciate the help.

28:02.071 --> 28:03.899
- We got 41 square miles
here.

28:03.943 --> 28:06.162
A lot of places
for Reg to hide.

28:06.206 --> 28:09.688
- Maybe we can narrow down
what he has in mind.

28:09.731 --> 28:11.385
- You don't know that!

28:11.428 --> 28:13.387
You can't promise
he won't hurt Rickey!

28:13.430 --> 28:14.997
- He won't.
Rickey's his only blood.

28:15.041 --> 28:16.433
- You're his blood too.

28:16.477 --> 28:17.913
I thought he was gonna
kill you.

28:17.957 --> 28:20.220
- I know my own son.
I raised him.

28:20.263 --> 28:22.657
- Your children will surprise
you, Mr. Waters.

28:22.701 --> 28:25.747
I'm sure you didn't raise him
to kill people, but he did.

28:25.791 --> 28:27.793
- What were you two
fighting about?

28:29.272 --> 28:30.752
- [sighs]

28:30.796 --> 28:32.798
Reg wanted Leonard to take him
somewhere.

28:32.841 --> 28:34.669
I don't know where.

28:34.713 --> 28:37.193
He said everything started
with what they did to Leonard.

28:37.237 --> 28:39.587
- Where did he want you
to take him, Mr. Waters?

28:39.630 --> 28:41.763
- Nowhere. He's always
stirring things up.

28:41.807 --> 28:43.156
That's his nature.

28:43.199 --> 28:45.724
Always looking
to blame other people.

28:48.074 --> 28:50.729
- I haven't seen one of those
in a long time.

28:52.818 --> 28:54.776
Saint Kateri Tekakwitha.

28:57.213 --> 29:00.782
Lily of the Mohawks.
Native American saint.

29:00.826 --> 29:03.263
- You're a nosy one,
aren't you?

29:03.306 --> 29:06.092
- Yeah, that's my nature.

29:09.878 --> 29:12.402
Sweetgrass.

29:12.446 --> 29:15.666
They'd give a cross wrapped
in sweetgrass to the Natives

29:15.710 --> 29:17.451
when they converted
to Catholicism.

29:17.494 --> 29:21.150
♪

29:21.194 --> 29:22.848
You still believe?

29:22.891 --> 29:25.372
- I believe in the Creator.

29:26.286 --> 29:29.115
- How old were you
when they gave you that?

29:30.029 --> 29:31.682
- I was just a boy.

29:34.207 --> 29:35.774
- You were
in residential school.

29:35.817 --> 29:37.340
- Ah, there you go.

29:37.384 --> 29:40.430
Just like him,
digging it all up.

29:42.345 --> 29:45.131
- Where's the sweetgrass that
was wrapped around that cross?

29:45.174 --> 29:46.785
- I don't know.

29:46.828 --> 29:49.265
- It was there this morning.
Maybe Reg took it.

29:49.309 --> 29:53.966
- Sweetgrass can be used as
an offering to purify a place,

29:54.009 --> 29:55.924
and that's where
he wanted you to take him:

29:55.968 --> 29:58.971
to where the abuse started,
to break the cycle.

29:59.014 --> 30:02.801
- Chasing ghosts.
Better to forget them.

30:04.541 --> 30:06.108
- What school did you go to?

30:06.152 --> 30:08.415
[somber music]

30:08.458 --> 30:10.896
♪

30:10.939 --> 30:12.680
- The Mush Hole.

30:14.203 --> 30:16.553
The St. Nicholas Institute
Residential School.

30:16.597 --> 30:18.599
Branchton, Ontario.
That's where he's going.

30:18.642 --> 30:21.123
- This is Barnes.
- Fire up the bird.

30:21.167 --> 30:23.125
Tell the Legat we need
immediate country clearance.

30:23.169 --> 30:25.824
We're heading to Canada.

30:25.867 --> 30:28.391
[suspenseful music]

30:34.093 --> 30:37.052
[somber music]

30:37.096 --> 30:44.103
♪

30:51.980 --> 30:53.852
- This is it.

30:56.637 --> 30:58.726
- This place
is creeping me out, Reg.

30:58.769 --> 31:00.510
- Come on.

31:00.554 --> 31:03.035
Just keep moving.

31:03.078 --> 31:10.085
♪

31:11.826 --> 31:13.915
This is the one.

31:13.959 --> 31:20.966
♪

31:32.934 --> 31:36.024
You know what that number is?

31:38.897 --> 31:40.420
That's our dad.

31:40.463 --> 31:42.509
- What do you mean?

31:48.732 --> 31:52.258
- This used to be a school
for kids like us.

31:53.912 --> 31:56.697
Mohawk kids.

31:58.699 --> 32:00.527
Our father was sent here.

32:00.570 --> 32:02.659
First thing they did
was cut off his hair,

32:02.703 --> 32:07.360
take away his name,
and give him a number.

32:07.403 --> 32:11.277
They'd say,
"363, go scrub the floor!

32:11.320 --> 32:15.368
363, stop crying
for your Ma and Pa!"

32:17.065 --> 32:18.980
- Dad was crying?

32:19.024 --> 32:21.287
- All the kids cried
all the time.

32:25.334 --> 32:27.380
They had no toys.

32:27.423 --> 32:31.036
They had no good food,
just mush.

32:31.079 --> 32:32.776
That's why they call this
place the Mush Hole.

32:32.820 --> 32:34.343
If they spoke Mohawk,

32:34.387 --> 32:36.041
the priests would put rags
soaked in kerosene

32:36.084 --> 32:37.607
in their mouth.

32:37.651 --> 32:39.348
If they fell asleep
during church service,

32:39.392 --> 32:42.699
the priests would touch them,
you know, abuse them.

32:44.484 --> 32:45.920
[sniffles]

32:47.226 --> 32:49.924
Those kids are all here now.

32:49.968 --> 32:52.187
They're ghosts,

32:52.231 --> 32:54.407
and we're gonna
do something for them.

32:54.450 --> 32:58.280
♪

32:58.324 --> 33:01.414
Here--write his name
over that number.

33:01.457 --> 33:04.765
Write our father's name.

33:04.808 --> 33:07.855
[can rattles]

33:13.034 --> 33:14.340
[inhales]

33:28.789 --> 33:31.835
[tense music]

33:31.879 --> 33:38.146
♪

33:38.190 --> 33:41.584
- We are green.
We are green. Go.

33:43.891 --> 33:46.154
- [murmurs orders]

33:47.068 --> 33:48.330
Go, go.

33:49.897 --> 33:51.333
[shotgun blast]
[Rickey yells]

33:53.074 --> 33:54.075
[shotgun cocks]

34:01.300 --> 34:03.737
[dark music]

34:03.780 --> 34:09.090
♪

34:21.450 --> 34:23.496
- What are you doing?

34:23.539 --> 34:26.803
- I'm making an offering.
- For the ghosts?

34:26.847 --> 34:29.241
- This one's just for us,
for our family.

34:29.284 --> 34:31.286
All the bad stuff
that happened here.

34:31.330 --> 34:33.767
They hurt our father so bad,
Rickey.

34:36.900 --> 34:39.207
- Did they hit him?

34:40.295 --> 34:43.820
- They beat his body, yeah,
but they beat his soul too.

34:43.864 --> 34:46.388
They told him his people
were low and dirty.

34:46.432 --> 34:48.738
They made him ashamed
until he hated himself.

34:48.782 --> 34:51.698
- Is that why he's so mean?

34:54.570 --> 34:58.139
- He's mean because he didn't
have parents to love him,

34:58.183 --> 35:00.315
not the way I see your mama
loves you.

35:00.359 --> 35:03.013
♪

35:03.057 --> 35:04.798
This place filled him
with rage--

35:04.841 --> 35:06.843
rage he passed on to me.

35:06.887 --> 35:09.107
But I won't let it happen
to you.

35:17.027 --> 35:18.942
Our family's been passing
the hurt in this place

35:18.986 --> 35:21.641
from one generation to the
next, but that stops today.

35:27.386 --> 35:30.345
[exhales]

35:34.567 --> 35:36.351
I make this offering

35:36.395 --> 35:39.441
to free this boy
from the curse of this place.

35:39.485 --> 35:40.747
[distant thud]

35:42.531 --> 35:46.970
Listen to me,
do exactly what I say.

35:47.014 --> 35:53.977
♪

36:13.736 --> 36:15.608
[distant thud]

36:27.837 --> 36:30.362
- Don't shoot us!
Please!

36:33.408 --> 36:35.671
- I won't hurt you, Rickey.

36:35.715 --> 36:37.238
Mr. Waters, let him go.

36:37.282 --> 36:39.806
- Me and Rickey
are walking out of here.

36:39.849 --> 36:41.764
- There's 50 police out there.

36:41.808 --> 36:45.725
SWAT, sharpshooters.
They won't let you go.

36:45.768 --> 36:47.901
- Get back.
Move!

36:47.944 --> 36:51.252
♪

36:51.296 --> 36:52.819
- Reg, I'm scared.

36:52.862 --> 36:55.865
- Don't be.
They won't shoot you.

36:55.909 --> 36:58.999
You all stay back or he dies.

36:59.042 --> 37:01.567
- You pull that trigger,
all bets are off.

37:01.610 --> 37:03.830
I'm gonna ask
one last time, Mr. Waters.

37:03.873 --> 37:06.180
Let the boy go.

37:06.224 --> 37:07.660
- [panting]

37:14.144 --> 37:15.972
- Send him to me.

37:16.016 --> 37:18.279
- [breathing hard]

37:19.846 --> 37:21.891
Go to him.
Go!

37:22.718 --> 37:25.939
- I don't want to, Reg.
I wanna stay with you.

37:25.982 --> 37:28.550
♪

37:28.594 --> 37:30.509
- Close your eyes.

37:31.945 --> 37:33.860
Do it, Rickey!

37:33.903 --> 37:36.036
Sing with me.

37:36.079 --> 37:37.820
Sing me out.

37:37.864 --> 37:40.867
♪

37:40.910 --> 37:42.303
- Don't do it, Reg.

37:42.347 --> 37:46.046
- [sings in Mohawk]

37:50.268 --> 37:54.750
[both sing in Mohawk]

37:56.491 --> 37:58.928
- [speaks in Mohawk]

38:01.366 --> 38:03.150
You're gonna fill that boy
with pain.

38:03.193 --> 38:04.760
- Who the hell are you?

38:04.804 --> 38:07.546
- Agent Clinton Skye.
I'm Kahnawake.

38:08.373 --> 38:09.983
I saw your offering.

38:10.026 --> 38:12.115
You broke the cycle of hurt.

38:12.159 --> 38:14.117
Don't start another one.

38:14.161 --> 38:17.077
- [speaks in Mohawk]

38:20.298 --> 38:23.910
- [speaks in Mohawk]

38:25.041 --> 38:26.956
He needs you
to show him the way.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.045
Help him stay on the Red Road.

38:29.089 --> 38:30.917
That's a good place to stand.

38:33.136 --> 38:36.618
[speaks in Mohawk]

38:36.662 --> 38:39.229
[somber music]

38:39.273 --> 38:42.320
- [pants]

38:42.363 --> 38:48.891
♪

38:56.290 --> 38:59.206
Give it to him.
Go.

38:59.249 --> 39:05.212
♪

39:05.255 --> 39:08.433
[handcuffs click]

39:08.476 --> 39:15.396
♪

39:15.440 --> 39:18.094
- We're clear, we're clear.
[indistinct radio chatter]

39:21.881 --> 39:24.797
- I put rings in one
and hairbands in the other.

39:24.840 --> 39:26.407
- Those belong to your father.

39:26.451 --> 39:27.843
- You shouldn't have
taken them.

39:27.887 --> 39:30.759
- I heard father.
Am I needed?

39:30.803 --> 39:33.501
- Well, I took these
to Diversity Day

39:33.545 --> 39:35.373
and everybody loved them,

39:35.416 --> 39:37.505
and I was wondering if I could
keep them in my room.

39:37.549 --> 39:39.246
- Those are our
wedding baskets.

39:39.289 --> 39:41.857
You took them to school?
You should've asked me first.

39:41.901 --> 39:44.643
- Well, sorry, but I got
an A for my presentation,

39:44.686 --> 39:47.167
and Uncle Clinton told me
all about them.

39:48.473 --> 39:50.300
- [chuckles]
What did I do?

39:50.344 --> 39:54.261
- So, can you tell me more
about them?

39:57.786 --> 39:59.440
- [scoffs]

40:01.616 --> 40:04.967
Your mother carried one
and it was filled with cloth,

40:05.011 --> 40:08.014
and I carried the other one
with a little cake inside,

40:08.057 --> 40:11.365
and then we exchanged them.

40:11.409 --> 40:15.456
♪

40:15.500 --> 40:18.024
- The cloth meant housekeeping.

40:18.067 --> 40:20.505
- House-making, not cleaning.

40:20.548 --> 40:23.116
- And the cake meant cooking.

40:23.159 --> 40:24.639
- Yeah.

40:24.683 --> 40:26.641
- The exchange is a promise.

40:26.685 --> 40:32.168
She makes the home,
and he provides the food.

40:32.212 --> 40:36.042
- The woman keeps a warm house
and the man hunts.

40:36.085 --> 40:38.827
But Jess doesn't hunt,
and Angelyne...

40:38.871 --> 40:43.092
♪

40:43.136 --> 40:45.225
- Angelyne wasn't made
for staying home.

40:46.661 --> 40:49.447
[cell phone rings]

40:50.535 --> 40:53.973
- So, can I put
my stuff in them?

40:55.496 --> 40:57.106
- Sure.

40:57.150 --> 40:59.500
- Yes!
Thanks, Dad.

40:59.544 --> 41:04.766
♪

41:04.810 --> 41:07.813
- They got a hit off
of Audrey Waters' DNA.

41:07.856 --> 41:10.076
Her remains were found
three months ago

41:10.119 --> 41:12.208
outside of New London,
Connecticut.

41:12.252 --> 41:13.775
The good news,

41:13.819 --> 41:16.517
she was processed
as a homicide.

41:16.561 --> 41:19.520
They found unknown DNA
under her fingernails,

41:19.564 --> 41:21.653
probably her assailant.

41:21.696 --> 41:23.959
- She went out fighting,
and now we can fight for her.

41:24.003 --> 41:26.571
- Let's bring her home.

41:26.614 --> 41:33.578
♪

41:37.407 --> 41:39.627
This isn't the end, okay?

41:39.671 --> 41:42.238
- We have evidence
that'll help find her killer.

41:42.282 --> 41:44.066
- We're not letting this go.

41:44.110 --> 41:46.765
- We'll tell Reginald.

41:46.808 --> 41:48.549
It'll mean a lot to him.

41:48.593 --> 41:51.552
- Reg's real name is Reginald?

41:51.596 --> 41:53.162
What's your real name, Dad?

41:53.206 --> 41:54.729
- You know.

41:54.773 --> 41:57.645
- I mean, the name
Grandma gave you.

41:57.689 --> 42:00.213
♪

42:00.256 --> 42:01.910
Kariwase.

42:01.954 --> 42:08.395
♪

42:14.140 --> 42:16.359
[speaks in Mohawk]

42:16.403 --> 42:23.410
♪

42:26.674 --> 42:28.502
[engine turns]

42:28.546 --> 42:35.553
♪
